access_key.Description:
The access key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

external_id.Description: The external ID to use when assuming the role. If omitted, no external ID is passed to the AssumeRole call.

policy.Description: The permissions applied when assuming a role. You cannot use, this policy to grant further permissions that are in excess to those of the,  role that is being assumed.

role_arn.Description: The ARN of an IAM role to assume prior to making API calls.

session_name.Description: The session name to use when assuming the role. If omitted, no session name is passed to the AssumeRole call.

max_retries.Description:
The maximum number of times an AWS API request is
being executed. If the API request still fails, an error is
thrown.

profile.Description:
The profile for API operations. If not set, the default profile
created with `aws configure` will be used.

region.Description:
The region where AWS operations will take place. Examples
are us-east-1, us-west-2, etc.

s3_force_path_style.Description:
Set this to true to force the request to use path-style addressing,
i.e., http://s3.amazonaws.com/BUCKET/KEY. By default, the S3 client will
use virtual hosted bucket addressing when possible
(http://BUCKET.s3.amazonaws.com/KEY). Specific to the Amazon S3 service.

secret_key.Description:
The secret key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

shared_credentials_file.Description:
The path to the shared credentials file. If not set
this defaults to ~/.aws/credentials.

skip_credentials_validation.Description: Skip the credentials validation via STS API. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have STS available/implemented.

skip_get_ec2_platforms.Description: Skip getting the supported EC2 platforms. Used by users that don't have ec2:DescribeAccountAttributes permissions.

skip_region_validation.Description: Skip static validation of region name. Used by users of alternative AWS-like APIs or users w/ access to regions that are not public (yet).

skip_requesting_account_id.Description: Skip requesting the account ID. Used for AWS API implementations that do not have IAM/STS API and/or metadata API.

token.Description:
session token. A session token is only required if you are
using temporary security credentials.

stage_key.Deprecated: Since the API Gateway usage plans feature was launched on August 11, 2016, usage plans are now required to associate an API key with an API stage

min_adjustment_step.Deprecated: Use min_adjustment_magnitude instead, otherwise you may see a perpetual diff on this resource.

timeout.Removed: This field has been removed. Please use build_timeout instead

number_of_connections.Deprecated: Use aws_dx_connection and aws_dx_connection_association resources instead. Default connections will be removed as part of LAG creation automatically in future versions.

reference_name.Deprecated: Please use attribute `creation_token' instead. This attribute might be removed in future releases.

secret.Deprecated: Please use a PGP key to encrypt

roles.Deprecated: Use `role` instead. Only a single role can be passed to an IAM Instance Profile

force_destroy.Description: Delete user even if it has non-Terraform-managed IAM access keys, login profile or MFA devices

block_device.Removed: Split out into three sub-types; see Changelog and Docs

subnet_id.Deprecated: Attribute subnet_id is deprecated on network_acl resources. Use subnet_ids instead

bucket_name.Deprecated: Use bucket_name in the 'logging' block instead

enable_logging.Deprecated: Use enable in the 'logging' block instead

s3_key_prefix.Deprecated: Use s3_key_prefix in the 'logging' block instead

failover.Removed: Now implemented as failover_routing_policy; see docs

weight.Removed: Now implemented as weighted_routing_policy; Please see https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/aws/r/route53_record.html

type.Description: Type of rule, ingress (inbound) or egress (outbound).

block_device.Removed: Split out into three sub-types; see Changelog and Docs

current.Deprecated: Defaults to current provider region if no other filtering is enabled
